projects.description: This repository provides a NUMA-aware benchmark for the GPU Adam optimizer, built on DeepSpeed. It evaluates performance on Linux systems with NUMA architectures and multiple NVIDIA GPUs, focusing on data transfer latencies between CPU memory (for tensors) and GPU computation.

projects.name: numa-cpu-adam-bench
projects.description: This repository offers a NUMA-aware benchmark for the CPU Adam optimizer, built on the DeepSpeed library. It assesses performance on Linux systems with NUMA architectures, using fp32 data types. The benchmark employs numactl for memory allocation across NUMA nodes and multi-processing to emulate concurrent optimizer updates in distributed training.
